1. *Krećem* se ka gradu. (I'm moving towards the city.)
2. Ovaj voz *kreće* za Beograd. (This train departs for Belgrade.)
3. Nisam siguran kada se *krećemo* na putovanje. (I'm not sure when we are starting our trip.)
4. Uvek se *kreće* u dobrom društvu. (You always move in good company.)
5. Kada se *krene* ujutru, ima manje gužve na ulici. (When you start in the morning, there is less traffic on the street.)
6. *Krenuli* smo na putovanje bez ikakvog plana. (We started our trip without any plan.)
7. Da li si već *krenuo* sa učenjem za ispit? (Have you already started studying for the exam?)
8. Njihova firma se *kreće* u usponu. (Their company is on the rise.)

Note: In Serbian language, the word "krećem" is used in different forms and tenses depending on the subject, context and tense. In the sentences above, I have used different forms of the word to demonstrate its versatility.